Long_Name: South Shore Intl College Prep High School
Student_Growth_Description: Student Growth measures the change in standardized test scores between two points in time, in this case between Spring 2014 and Spring 2015. This growth is compared to the average national growth for schools that had similar scores in 2014. A 50th percentile score means the school grew at the same rate as the national average.
Student_Attainment_Description: Student Attainment measures how well the school performed on standardized tests at a single point in time, in this case Spring 2015. This school's scores are compared to national average scores. A 50th percentile score means the school is performing at the same level as the national average school.
Culture_Climate_Description: Results are based on student and teacher responses to the My Voice, My School 5Essentials survey. For more information on this survey and other measures of school culture and climate visit https://cps.5-essentials.org/2015
Healthy_School_Certification_Description: This school has not achieved Healthy School Certified Status. Moving forward, the district will no longer use the HealthierUS School Challenge to determine a school’s status. To better measure a school’s commitment to a safe and healthy learning environment, schools must earn four badges to become Healthy CPS beginning SY16-17. Learn more by visiting www.cps.edu/healthycps.
Creative_School_Certification_Descriptio: This school has an arts designation of Incomplete Data, meaning it may or may not meet the goals and priorities of the CPS Arts Education Plan, but has insufficient data available to complete an assessment. To learn more, visit: www.cpsarts.org/creative-schools-certification.

Supportive_School_Award_Desc: This school is in the process of being reviewed for its implementation of supports for social and emotional learning (SEL) and will receive a rating next year. For information about this new certification, visit www.cps.edu/sel

Student_Attainment_Description: Student Attainment measures how well the school performed on standardized tests at a single point in time, in this case Spring 2015. This school's scores are compared to national average scores. A 50th percentile score means the school is performing at the same level as the national average school.

Healthy_School_Certification_Description: This school has achieved Healthy School Certified Status. Student_Attainment_Description: Student Attainment measures how well the school performed on standardized tests at a single point in time, in this case Spring 2015. This school's scores are compared to national average scores. A 50th percentile score means the school is performing at the same level as the national average school.
Culture_Climate_Description: Results are based on student and teacher responses to the My Voice, My School 5Essentials survey. For more information on this survey and other measures of school culture and climate visit https://cps.5-essentials.org/2015
Healthy_School_Certification_Description: This school has not achieved Healthy School Certified Status. Moving forward, the district will no longer use the HealthierUS School Challenge to determine a school’s status. To better measure a school’s commitment to a safe and healthy learning environment, schools must earn four badges to become Healthy CPS beginning SY16-17. Learn more by visiting www.cps.edu/healthycps.
Creative_School_Certification_Descriptio: This school has an arts designation of Incomplete Data, meaning it may or may not meet the goals and priorities of the CPS Arts Education Plan, but has insufficient data available to complete an assessment. To learn more, visit: www.cpsarts.org/creative-schools-certification.

Student_Growth_Description: Student Growth measures the change in standardized test scores between two points in time, in this case between Spring 2014 and Spring 2015. Student_Attainment_Description: Student Attainment measures how well the school performed on standardized tests at a single point in time, in this case Spring 2015. Student_Growth_Description: Student Growth measures the change in standardized test scores between two points in time, in this case between Spring 2014 and Spring 2015. This growth is compared to the average national growth for schools that had similar scores in 2014. A 50th percentile score means the school grew at the same rate as the national average.
Student_Attainment_Description: Student Attainment measures how well the school performed on standardized tests at a single point in time, in this case Spring 2015. This school's scores are compared to national average scores. A 50th percentile score means the school is performing at the same level as the national average school.

Healthy_School_Certification_Description: This school has achieved Healthy School Certified Status. Learn more by visiting www.cps.edu/healthycps.

Learn more by visiting www.cps.edu/healthycps.

Student_Attainment_Description: Student Attainment measures how well the school performed on standardized tests at a single point in time, in this case Spring 2015. Culture_Climate_Description: Results are based on student and teacher responses to the My Voice, My School 5Essentials survey. For more information on this survey and other measures of school culture and climate visit https://cps.5-essentials.org/2015
Healthy_School_Certification_Description: This school has achieved Healthy School Certified Status. Moving forward, the district will no longer use the HealthierUS School Challenge to determine a school’s status. To better measure a school’s commitment to a safe and healthy learning environment, schools must earn four badges to become Healthy CPS beginning SY16-17. Learn more by visiting www.cps.edu/healthycps.
Creative_School_Certification_Descriptio: This school is Excelling in the arts. Student_Attainment_Description: Student Attainment measures how well the school performed on standardized tests at a single point in time, in this case Spring 2015. This school's scores are compared to national average scores. A 50th percentile score means the school is performing at the same level as the national average school.

Healthy_School_Certification_Description: This school has not achieved Healthy School Certified Status. For more information on this survey and other measures of school culture and climate, visit: https://cps.5-essentials.org/2015
Supportive_School_Award_Desc: This school is in the process of being reviewed for its implementation of supports for social and emotional learning (SEL) and will receive a rating next year. For information about this new certification, visit www.cps.edu/sel

Student_Growth_Description: Student Growth measures the change in standardized test scores between two points in time, in this case between Spring 2014 and Spring 2015. This growth is compared to the average national growth for schools that had similar scores in 2014. A 50th percentile score means the school grew at the same rate as the national average.
Student_Attainment_Description: Student Attainment measures how well the school performed on standardized tests at a single point in time, in this case Spring 2015. This school's scores are compared to national average scores. A 50th percentile score means the school is performing at the same level as the national average school.
Culture_Climate_Description: Results are based on student and teacher responses to the My Voice, My School 5Essentials survey. For more information on this survey and other measures of school culture and climate visit https://cps.5-essentials.org/2015
Healthy_School_Certification_Description: This school has not achieved Healthy School Certified Status. Moving forward, the district will no longer use the HealthierUS School Challenge to determine a school’s status. To better measure a school’s commitment to a safe and healthy learning environment, schools must earn four badges to become Healthy CPS beginning SY16-17. Learn more by visiting www.cps.edu/healthycps.
Creative_School_Certification_Descriptio: This school is Excelling in the arts. To learn more, visit: www.cpsarts.org/creative-schools-certification.

Student_Growth_Description: Student Growth measures the change in standardized test scores between two points in time, in this case between Spring 2014 and Spring 2015. This growth is compared to the average national growth for schools that had similar scores in 2014. A 50th percentile score means the school grew at the same rate as the national average.
Student_Attainment_Description: Student Attainment measures how well the school performed on standardized tests at a single point in time, in this case Spring 2015. This school's scores are compared to national average scores. A 50th percentile score means the school is performing at the same level as the national average school.

Student_Attainment_Description: Student Attainment measures how well the school performed on standardized tests at a single point in time, in this case Spring 2015. This school's scores are compared to national average scores. A 50th percentile score means the school is performing at the same level as the national average school.
Culture_Climate_Description: Results are based on student and teacher responses to the My Voice, My School 5Essentials survey. For more information on this survey and other measures of school culture and climate visit https://cps.5-essentials.org/2015
Healthy_School_Certification_Description: This school has achieved Healthy School Certified Status. Moving forward, the district will no longer use the HealthierUS School Challenge to determine a school’s status. To better measure a school’s commitment to a safe and healthy learning environment, schools must earn four badges to become Healthy CPS beginning SY16-17. Learn more by visiting www.cps.edu/healthycps.
Creative_School_Certification_Descriptio: This school is Excelling in the arts. It meets the goals and priorities outlined in the CPS Arts Education Plan, including Staffing & Instruction, Partnerships, Community & Culture, and Budget & Planning. To learn more, visit: www.cpsarts.org/creative-schools-certification.

This growth is compared to the average national growth for schools that had similar scores in 2014. A 50th percentile score means the school grew at the same rate as the national average.
Student_Attainment_Description: Student Attainment measures how well the school performed on standardized tests at a single point in time, in this case Spring 2015. This school's scores are compared to national average scores. A 50th percentile score means the school is performing at the same level as the national average school.
Culture_Climate_Description: Results are based on student and teacher responses to the My Voice, My School 5Essentials survey. For more information on this survey and other measures of school culture and climate visit https://cps.5-essentials.org/2015
Healthy_School_Certification_Description: This school has not achieved Healthy School Certified Status. For more information on this survey and other measures of school culture and climate, visit: https://cps.5-essentials.org/2015
Supportive_School_Award_Desc: This school is in the process of being reviewed for its implementation of supports for social and emotional learning (SEL) and will receive a rating next year. For information about this new certification, visit www.cps.edu/sel

Student_Growth_Description: Student Growth measures the change in standardized test scores between two points in time, in this case between Spring 2014 and Spring 2015. This growth is compared to the average national growth for schools that had similar scores in 2014. A 50th percentile score means the school grew at the same rate as the national average.
Student_Attainment_Description: Student Attainment measures how well the school performed on standardized tests at a single point in time, in this case Spring 2015. This school's scores are compared to national average scores. A 50th percentile score means the school is performing at the same level as the national average school.
Culture_Climate_Description: Results are based on student and teacher responses to the My Voice, My School 5Essentials survey. For more information on this survey and other measures of school culture and climate visit https://cps.5-essentials.org/2015
Healthy_School_Certification_Description: This school has not achieved Healthy School Certified Status. Moving forward, the district will no longer use the HealthierUS School Challenge to determine a school’s status. To better measure a school’s commitment to a safe and healthy learning environment, schools must earn four badges to become Healthy CPS beginning SY16-17. Learn more by visiting www.cps.edu/healthycps.
Creative_School_Certification_Descriptio: This school is Emerging in the arts. It rarely meets the goals and priorities outlined in the CPS Arts Education Plan including Staffing & Instruction, Partnerships, Community & Culture, and Budget & Planning. To learn more, visit: www.cpsarts.org/creative-schools-certification.

To better measure a school’s commitment to a safe and healthy learning environment, schools must earn four badges to become Healthy CPS beginning SY16-17. Learn more by visiting www.cps.edu/healthycps.
Creative_School_Certification_Descriptio: This school is Developing in the arts. It occasionally meets the goals and priorities of the CPS Arts Education Plan including Staffing & Instruction, Partnerships, Community & Culture and Budget & Planning. To learn more, visit: www.cpsarts.org/creative-schools-certification.
Empty_Progress_Report_Message: This School Progress Report is currently under development. In the meantime, click here to access all schools' 2016-2017 School Quality Rating Policy (SQRP) and Accountability Status data.
School_Survey_Rating_Description: This school is “Well-Organized for Improvement” which means that the school has a very strong culture and climate, suggesting that the school is set up for success. Results are based on student and teacher responses to the My Voice, My School 5Essentials survey. For more information on this survey and other measures of school culture and climate, visit: https://cps.5-essentials.org/2015
Supportive_School_Award_Desc: This school is in the process of being reviewed for its implementation of supports for social and emotional learning (SEL) and will receive a rating next year. For information about this new certification, visit www.cps.edu/sel

Student_Growth_Description: Student Growth measures the change in standardized test scores between two points in time, in this case between Spring 2014 and Spring 2015. This growth is compared to the average national growth for schools that had similar scores in 2014. A 50th percentile score means the school grew at the same rate as the national average.
Student_Attainment_Description: Student Attainment measures how well the school performed on standardized tests at a single point in time, in this case Spring 2015. This school's scores are compared to national average scores. A 50th percentile score means the school is performing at the same level as the national average school.
Culture_Climate_Description: Results are based on student and teacher responses to the My Voice, My School 5Essentials survey. For more information on this survey and other measures of school culture and climate visit https://cps.5-essentials.org/2015
Healthy_School_Certification_Description: This school has not achieved Healthy School Certified Status. Moving forward, the district will no longer use the HealthierUS School Challenge to determine a school’s status. To better measure a school’s commitment to a safe and healthy learning environment, schools must earn four badges to become Healthy CPS beginning SY16-17. Learn more by visiting www.cps.edu/healthycps.
Creative_School_Certification_Descriptio: This school has an arts designation of Incomplete Data, meaning it may or may not meet the goals and priorities of the CPS Arts Education Plan, but has insufficient data available to complete an assessment. To learn more, visit: www.cpsarts.org/creative-schools-certification.

Student_Attainment_Description: Student Attainment measures how well the school performed on standardized tests at a single point in time, in this case Spring 2015. This school's scores are compared to national average scores. A 50th percentile score means the school is performing at the same level as the national average school.
Culture_Climate_Description: Results are based on student and teacher responses to the My Voice, My School 5Essentials survey. For more information on this survey and other measures of school culture and climate visit https://cps.5-essentials.org/2015
Healthy_School_Certification_Description: This school has not achieved Healthy School Certified Status. Moving forward, the district will no longer use the HealthierUS School Challenge to determine a school’s status. To better measure a school’s commitment to a safe and healthy learning environment, schools must earn four badges to become Healthy CPS beginning SY16-17. Learn more by visiting www.cps.edu/healthycps.
Creative_School_Certification_Descriptio: This school is Developing in the arts. It occasionally meets the goals and priorities of the CPS Arts Education Plan including Staffing & Instruction, Partnerships, Community & Culture and Budget & Planning. To learn more, visit: www.cpsarts.org/creative-schools-certification.

This growth is compared to the average national growth for schools that had similar scores in 2014. A 50th percentile score means the school grew at the same rate as the national average.
Student_Attainment_Description: Student Attainment measures how well the school performed on standardized tests at a single point in time, in this case Spring 2015. This school's scores are compared to national average scores. A 50th percentile score means the school is performing at the same level as the national average school.
Culture_Climate_Description: Results are based on student and teacher responses to the My Voice, My School 5Essentials survey. For more information on this survey and other measures of school culture and climate visit https://cps.5-essentials.org/2015
Healthy_School_Certification_Description: This school has not achieved Healthy School Certified Status. Moving forward, the district will no longer use the HealthierUS School Challenge to determine a school’s status. To better measure a school’s commitment to a safe and healthy learning environment, schools must earn four badges to become Healthy CPS beginning SY16-17. Learn more by visiting www.cps.edu/healthycps.
Creative_School_Certification_Descriptio: This school has an arts designation of Incomplete Data, meaning it may or may not meet the goals and priorities of the CPS Arts Education Plan, but has insufficient data available to complete an assessment. To learn more, visit: www.cpsarts.org/creative-schools-certification.
